==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|abisme}} from {{etyl|VL.}} *{{term||abyssimus}}, the superlative of {{term|abyssus||an abyss, a bottomless gulf|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἄβυσσος|tr=abyssos||without bottom}}, from {{term|sc=polytonic|ἀ-||tr=a-|not|lang=grc}}+ {{term|sc=polytonic|βυσσός||tr=bysso|depth|lang=grc}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Pertaining to, or resembling an [[abyss]]; [[bottomless]]; [[unending]]; [[profound]]; [[fathomless]]; [[immeasurable]].
#* Carlyle
#*: Geology gives one the same '''abysmal''' extent of time that astronomy does of space.
# Extremely [[bad]].

====Usage notes====
* Nouns to which "abysmal" is often applied: ignorance, record, performance, poverty, conditions, quality, perplexity, result.

